{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"23":{"eng-name":"Chapters on Shares of Inheritance","ara-name":"كتاب الفرائض"}},"section_detail":{"23":{"hadithnumber_first":2719,"hadithnumber_last":2752,"arabicnumber_first":2719,"arabicnumber_last":2752}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":2733,"arabicnumber":2733,"text":"It was narrated from ‘Aishah that the freed slave of the Prophet (ﷺ) fell from a palm tree and died. He left behind wealth but he had no child or close relative. The Prophet (ﷺ) said:“Give his legacy to a man from his village.”","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Hasan"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Hasan"}],"reference":{"book":23,"hadith":15},"chapter":{"id":7,"ara-name":"باب مِيرَاثِ الْوَلاَءِ","eng-name":"Inheritance of Wala’","isFirstHadith":false}}]}